{"TopicId":149630,"ForumId":35,"TopicTitle":"Fairing interstage node calculator","CreatedByName":"IronCretin","CreatedById":158162,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-11T02:50:45Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"IronCretin","CreatedById":158162,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-11T02:50:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:24px;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://ironcretin.github.io/Fairing-Node-Helper/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EFairing node calculator\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, 1.2 adds cool new fairing interstage nodes \u0026amp; trusses, which is awesome.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022w4D8O1E.png?2\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/w4D8O1E.png?2\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, they require a lot of tedious math to properly add to your parts, or they won\u0027t be aligned properly, which is not awesome.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022hm8LsHP.png?1\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/hm8LsHP.png?1\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, to help people (like me) add nodes to modded fairings, I\u0027ve created \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://ironcretin.github.io/Fairing-Node-Helper/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ethis nifty little tool\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo use it, put the diameter of the fairing base into the \u0022Base size\u0022 input, the vertical position of your fairing\u0027s\u00A0top node into the \u0022Top node position\u0022 box, and hit the button. Then simply copy the resulting code into your part config, and enjoy!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReport all\u00A0issues and feedback at the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/IronCretin/Fairing-Node-Helper\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EGithub repo\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-11T02:56:44Z\u0022 title=\u002210/11/2016 02:56  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 11, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by IronCretin\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stone Blue","CreatedById":77721,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-10T21:19:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow... HOW did I never see this before, or catch mention of it in The Dev Hole??... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nDefinately adding this to my toolbox... Should compliment Felbourn\u0027s NodeHelper mod pertty well...\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanx, Komrade! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}